<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="398" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                        <head>398. Telegram 1339 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d398fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/12–255.
                                Confidential. Drafted by Jacobson; cleared in IAD and
                            CA.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-12-02">December 2, 1955, 6:54
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d398-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d398-1"/>
                        <p>1339. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>In view pertinent Peiping broadcasts transmitted Geneva in full by FBIS,
                            Department believes it unnecessary continue weekly telegrams summarizing
                            ChiCom propaganda. Therefore unless you request continuation no further
                            weekly summary will be issued.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1"><hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>